Craig S. Ivey  President of Consolidated Edison Company of New York Inc, Consolidated Edison, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships54$4,201,942As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Craig S. Ivey has been the President of Consolidated Edison Co. of New York Inc. at Electric Power Research Institute, Inc. since December 2009. Mr. Ivey serves as a Senior Vice President of Virginia Electric and Power Company. He joined Consolidated Edison from Dominion Resources Services Company, where he served as Senior Vice President of Transmission and Distribution from August 2007 to September 2009, Senior Vice President of Electric Distribution from April ... 2006 to August 2007 and Vice President of Electric Operations from September 2004 to April 2006. He serves as a Trustee of Hospital for Special Surgery, Inc. He has been a Director of Electric Power Research Institute, Inc since 2012. Mr. Ivey holds a B.S. in Electrical Engineering from North Carolina State University. He has completed executive education programs at the University of Michigan and Harvard University.Read Full Background




