Corporate Leadership


Craig S. Ivey






Craig S. Ivey







                        President, Consolidated Edison Company of New York
                    








            Craig S. Ivey is president of Consolidated Edison Company of New York; he became president on November 1, 2009.

Between 2007 and 2009, Mr. Ivey was senior vice president for Transmission and Distribution at Dominion Resources. He joined Dominion in 1985 and became the general manager of Distribution Operations in 1998, a vice president in 2000, and senior vice president in 2006.

Mr. Ivey holds a B.S. in Electrical Engineering from North Carolina State University. He has completed executive education programs at the University of Michigan and Harvard University.           
        







